## Architecture Decisions

- **Token-efficiency architecture** — all documents are pre-processed (OCR, chunking, entity extraction) before being passed to Claude; raw PDFs are never sent directly to the API
- **Accord Project** — contract templates follow Accord/Cicero standard for machine-readable legal logic; do not invent custom contract schemas
- **LexNLP** — used for clause extraction, date/amount parsing, and jurisdiction detection from raw contract text
- **ContextGem** — handles contract intelligence layer (risk flagging, clause comparison, anomaly detection)
- **SwiftCPQ** — powers quoting/pricing logic for proposal generation; integrates upstream of contract creation
- **DocuSeal** — self-hostable eSignature; preferred over DocuSign for cost and data control
- **AWS Textract + Comprehend** — primary document ingestion pipeline; Comprehend handles entity recognition post-OCR
- **Claude API** — final structuring, summarization, and clause generation; always called from `services/ai_service.py`

